author: AirPano VR
description:
Welcome to Vladivostok, a port city on the coast of the Japan Sea and Russia's gateway to the Asia-Pacific region. 

Vladivostok was founded in the second half of the 19th century and was originally intended to be a Russian naval base on the Pacific coast. Over time, it has evolved and gradually turned into a large city with access to the sea. However, it still holds secrets of the past.

Don't forget that this is 360° video: you can change the angle of view.
